> speak to dusty den

> speak to dusty den
Dusty Den greets you warmly as if you were an old friend.  "Hey there!"  he cries as he sees you.  "You can't do me a favour, can you?  I've not had my delivery - I was expecting a barrel of ale, but it hasn't arrived.  If you can find a way to pick it up for me and drop it in the cellar I'd be very grateful. I'll leave the cellar open."
> speak to dusty den

> speak to dusty den
You engage in a friendly conversation with Dusty Den.  He doesn't seem a bad chap and although you don't learn much from chatting to him, he does give you a free bottle of beer.

Miss Harlott sniffles slightly as she walks round the bar.
> x miss harlott

> x miss harlott
The very efficient barmaid of the Tavern.
 She is of average build and average height. She is NOT a stereotype!
> x bar

> x bar
A large wooden counter which acts as the bar of this establishment.  Dusty Den stands behind it and looks at you curiously.
Sitting on the bar is a beermat.
