You hold the smelling salts under Vidal Monsoon's nose and see it begin to twitch.  The strong smell drifts up his nose and reawakens him with a start, knocking over the pot of smelling salts and breaking it.

"Oh..." he says disorientated.  "Did I... did I pass out?" "Yes," you assure him, putting a comforting hand on his shoulder.  "The beer was stronger than I thought."

"Thanks for waking me up. Have I been unconscious long?" "No," you lie.

"Ah.  Maybe I should sit down for a while," he suggests.  He goes to turn away, but then turns back to you after producing something from his inside pocket.  "I suppose I should thank you for making sure I was ok.  Take this.  It's a voucher for a complimentary wash, cut and blow dry."

Vidal staggers a little unsteadily as he hands it to you.  "I really need to sit down." With that, he collapses into the salon chair and falls asleep.
