> speak to miss sharples

> speak to miss sharples
"It's a terrible business," bemoans Miss Sharples.

"Yes, it is," you agree.  "Have you any idea who did it?"

"No, Inspector Kojak asked me to come round and look at the crime scene."

"Have you discovered anything?"

"The murder weapon was most likely a candlestick.  From a tissue found at the scene, we believe the murderer has a cold."
> give ball of wool to miss sharples

> give ball of wool to miss sharples
You hand the wool to Miss Sharples and she whips out her knitting needles and begins to knit.  You are amazed at the speed she wields her needles.  However the wooden needles she is using snap due to her extreme speed.

"Oh dear," she cries.  "I'm so sorry.  My needles have broken."

"Is there anything I can do?"  you ask.

"Well I normally use metal ones.  They are much stronger.  If you can find me some I'll happily finish this for you."
